Reasoning: The paper deals with computational social choice theory, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence and game theory. The focus is on the complexity of the Possible Winner and Coalitional Manipulation problems, which are algorithmic problems related to voting. This makes cs.GT (Game Theory and Economics), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses fixed parameter tractable algorithms, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems).
